# Documentation Update Rule

- When behavior, architecture, or setup changes:
  - update `README.md` (quick usage)
  - update `RUNBOOK.md` (operational steps/troubleshooting)
  - update `SD-DESIGN.md` / `SD-ARCHITECTURE.md` when design/architecture changes
  - if a **`slidev/`** deck exists locally, update **`slidev/slides.md`** (and related deck files) per **`slidev-deck.mdc`** so diagrams and flow match the code end-to-end
- Append a new entry to `PROMPTS.md` for meaningful user requests and resulting changes.
- Keep entries chronological and concise.
